Class YADABufferedReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.io.Reader

        • com.novartis.opensource.yada.io.YADABufferedReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Readable

    public class YADABufferedReader
extends BufferedReader
    A subclass of BufferedReader which contains methods for returning a line of input as a JSONObject
    Author:
    David Varon

    • Method Detail

      • setFileHelper

        private void setFileHelper(FileHelper helper)
                    throws YADAIOException
        Called by the constructor to set the instance variable, this method also, in turn sets the the current object (a subclass of Reader) as an instance variable in the helper (via FileHelper.setReader(Reader)). It also calls FileHelper.setHeaders()
        Parameters:
        helper - the FileHelper subclass to handle headers
        Throws:
        YADAIOException - when helper can't set the headers
        See Also:
        FileHelper

      • readLine2JSON

        public org.json.JSONObject readLine2JSON()
                                  throws YADAIOException
        Alternative to BufferedReader.readLine() which will wrap content of a line in JSON using corresponding indexed column headers as keys.
        Returns:
        a json object containing a line of content with corresponding column headers as keys and column values as values.
        Throws:
        YADAIOException - when the content can't be read, or wrapped in JSON successfully
